  "text": "The first time an esophagocutaneous fistula was used for access to insert a PEG tube was reported by [CITATION_1] [1], when they described 1 case among 50 successful PEGs in HNC patients. Since then, only a few reports have been described in the medical literature. Our aim was to report our experience with use of a postoperative cervical fistula as an alternative access route for PEG tube placement in HNC patients with obstructive lesions of the oropharyngeal region.",
